# TYPING RULE: impl-Trait position determines universal-vs-existential
# quantifier desugaring.
#
# Prior art: RFC 1522 ("Conservative impl Trait") and RFC 1951 ("Expand
# impl Trait") — argument-position `impl Trait` desugars to a caller-chosen,
# universally quantified anonymous generic parameter (`fn f(x: impl Trait)`
# is exactly `fn f<T: Trait>(x: T)`); return-position `impl Trait` desugars
# to a callee-chosen, existentially quantified opaque type (the concrete
# type is picked once by the function body and hidden from every caller,
# who knows only the trait bound). This universal/existential (∀/∃) reading
# is the standard account both RFCs and the language team's own design
# writing use for abstract/opaque return types, tracing to Mitchell &
# Plotkin, "Abstract Types Have Existential Type", ACM TOPLAS 10(3), 1988 —
# the paper that first formalized "a module exporting an abstract type" as
# an existential-type elimination, which is exactly what a function
# returning `impl Trait` does at the signature level.
#
# ggen template patterns this checks (the corpus's only two impl-Trait
# occurrences, one of each position — re-verified 2026-07-21 directly
# against the live template files, not carried over from prose unverified):
#   - packs/affidavit-pack/templates/affidavit_types.rs.tmpl:77
#     `pub fn from_hex(hex: impl Into<String>) -> Self` — ARGUMENT position
#     — gec:ImplTrait_from_hex_hex — must derive gec:UniversalQuantifier
#   - packs/cargo-cicd-pack/templates/cargo_cicd_catalog.rs.tmpl:75
#     `-> impl Iterator<Item = &'static CargoCicdCommand> + '_` — RETURN
#     position — gec:ImplTrait_commands_for_noun_return — must derive
#     gec:ExistentialQuantifier
#
# Target vocabulary: gec:quantifierKind / gec:QuantifierKind (ontology.ttl
# §10), added specifically so this CONSTRUCT rule has somewhere to write its
# derived classification — never hand-asserted on a grounded fixture.
#
# Verified 2026-07-21: running this CONSTRUCT against
# ontology.ttl+fixtures/gec-facts.ttl produces exactly 2 triples, matching
# the two grounded instances above with the expected quantifier kind each.
PREFIX gec: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/rust-dialect#>
CONSTRUCT {
  ?it gec:quantifierKind ?kind .
}
WHERE {
  ?it a gec:ImplTraitType ; gec:implPosition ?pos .
  BIND(IF(?pos = gec:ArgumentPosition, gec:UniversalQuantifier, gec:ExistentialQuantifier) AS ?kind)
}
